This code is based on the huggingface tutorial on how to fine-tune a VIT model with some minor changes

################### INSTALLATION AND EXECUTION COMMANDS ###################

A) How to Run this Code
you need python 3.10 and pytorch 2.2

install libraries (better to use a python virtual environment or an conda environment)
- pip install datasets transformers accelerate torch scikit-learn matplotlib tensorboard codecarbon TensorFlow pillow==9.5.0 tf-keras

B) how to run this code (we use the accelerate lib to execute it faster)
accelerate lauch filename.py

c) How to create the charts of the results
tensorboard --logdir /absolute path here --host 0.0.0.0 --port 6006

(example) tensorboard --logdir/workspace/experiment/learning_rate --host 0.0.0.0 --port 6006

d) how to check NVIDIA resourse
watch -n 1 nvidia-smi

 

